modules.description: Processes and modifies parsing actions and inherited values during lexical analysis, handling position tracking and debug information. Operates on lists, arrays, hash tables, and custom parser state structures. Used to convert rule lists into mapping structures, manage symbol inheritance, and interface with parsing devices.

Processes and generates parse tables from grammar definitions using LALR(1) algorithm. Operates on abstract syntax trees and production rules represented as lists and tuples. Used to build custom parsers for domain-specific languages and configuration file formats.

manages parsing actions and inherited values by manipulating lists, arrays, hash tables, and custom state structures. It tracks positions, handles debug data, and converts rule lists into mapping structures. It supports symbol inheritance and interacts with parsing devices. Examples include modifying action semantics, tracking token positions, and managing symbol scope during analysis.
